content.description: Start with very thin face moves and a low foot on the ledge down and to the right. Pulling on and the first few moves are a V5ish sequence on unapparent holds. Once one gains the obvious, thin, crimp downpull up a few feet and to the right, a moment can be had. Keep it together for the second half of the problem, ~V3 in its own, finishing up high.
content.protection: Depends on the climber but a pad or 2 should work.
content.location:
Start immediately to the north of "Aretes Away" V2, as listed in

Bouldering Colorado

by Bob Horan. Walk into the stone room just north of overhanging west face. The problem is the first climb possible past the arete.
